                            <comment id="13820823" author="daijy" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 02:01:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Agree with #1. For #2, seems that&apos;s not the intention for the current code. Though we can see it in POPackage, but the code path is not in use. But since we plan to clean up STATUS_NULL -&amp;gt; (null, STATUS_OK), we are free to redefine the meaning for STATUS_NULL (a different name might be better).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13821904" author="daijy" created="Wed, 13 Nov 2013 22:10:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think #2 is also fine. We do use it to signal a tuple need to be skipped in POForEach (which wrongly changed by &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3060&quot; title=&quot;FLATTEN in nested foreach fails when the input contains an empty bag&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3060&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3060&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-3570&quot; title=&quot;Rollback PIG-3060&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PIG-3570&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PIG-3570&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; roll it back). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when we use STATUS_NULL to signal a skip tuple, STATUS_NULL need to go through the rest of pipeline. We might consider to contain STATUS_NULL in the operator in the future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13822732" author="mwagner" created="Thu, 14 Nov 2013 18:32:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch for option #2. I&apos;ve also created a RB: &lt;a href=&quot;https://reviews.apache.org/r/15524/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://reviews.apache.org/r/15524/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13823333" author="cheolsoo" created="Fri, 15 Nov 2013 06:07:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thank you for cleaning up this mess!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The patch looks good to me. I am running unit and e2e tests now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
